1
00:04:42,401 --> 00:04:43,859
No!

2
00:05:17,103 --> 00:05:19,767
There she is. There she is.

3
00:05:28,981 --> 00:05:30,605
There she is.

4
00:14:18,777 --> 00:14:20,768
Ladies and gentlemen,

5
00:14:20,913 --> 00:14:25,043
l've traveled over half our
state to be here tonight.

6
00:14:25,150 --> 00:14:27,675
l couldn't get away sooner
because my new well was coming in

7
00:14:27,786 --> 00:14:30,687
at Coyote Hills
and l had to see about it.

8
00:14:30,789 --> 00:14:33,781
That well is now flowing
at 2,000 barrels

9
00:14:33,926 --> 00:14:37,089
and it's paying me an income
of $5,000 a week.

10
00:14:37,763 --> 00:14:39,175
l have two others drilling

11
00:14:39,175 --> 00:14:41,062
and l have 16 producing
at Antelope,

12
00:14:41,199 --> 00:14:43,425
so, ladies and gentlemen

13
00:14:43,425 --> 00:14:45,602
if l say l'm an oilman,
you will agree.

14
00:14:48,440 --> 00:14:51,102
Now, you have a great
chance here,

15
00:14:51,243 --> 00:14:54,110
but bear in mind you could lose
it all if you're not careful.

16
00:14:54,246 --> 00:14:56,612
Out of all men that beg for
a chance to drill your lots,

17
00:14:56,748 --> 00:14:59,945
maybe one in twenty
will be oilmen.

18
00:15:00,052 --> 00:15:01,280
The rest will be speculators,

19
00:15:01,386 --> 00:15:03,911
that's men trying to get
between you and the oilmen

20
00:15:04,022 --> 00:15:07,617
to get some of the money that
ought, by rights, come to you.

21
00:15:07,726 --> 00:15:09,499
Even if you find one that
has money

22
00:15:09,499 --> 00:15:10,661
and means to drill,

23
00:15:10,796 --> 00:15:13,230
he'll maybe know nothing
about drilling.

24
00:15:13,332 --> 00:15:15,300
He'll have to hire the job
out on contract,

25
00:15:15,434 --> 00:15:18,232
and then you're depending
on a contractor,

26
00:15:18,337 --> 00:15:19,395
who'll rush the job through

27
00:15:19,504 --> 00:15:21,597
so he can get another contract
just as quick as he can.

28
00:15:21,707 --> 00:15:23,265
This is the way that this works.

29
00:15:23,375 --> 00:15:26,640
What is your offer?
We're wasting time.

30
00:15:26,945 --> 00:15:27,912
Please!

31
00:15:31,149 --> 00:15:33,083
l do my own drilling.

32
00:15:33,752 --> 00:15:35,863
And the men that work for me,

33
00:15:35,863 --> 00:15:37,620
work for me and they are
men l know.

34
00:15:37,756 --> 00:15:41,453
l make it my business to be
there and to see their work.

35
00:15:41,593 --> 00:15:43,112
l don't lose my tools in the hole

36
00:15:43,112 --> 00:15:44,653
and spend months fishing for them.

37
00:15:44,796 --> 00:15:45,922
l don't botch the cementing off

38
00:15:46,031 --> 00:15:49,592
and let water in the hole
and ruin the whole lease.

39
00:15:49,735 --> 00:15:51,726
l'm a family man.

40
00:15:51,837 --> 00:15:52,800
l run a family business

41
00:15:52,800 --> 00:15:56,467
This is my son and my partner,
H.W. Plainview.

42
00:15:57,476 --> 00:15:59,737
We offer you the bond of family

43
00:15:59,737 --> 00:16:02,277
that very few oilmen
can understand.

44
00:16:04,249 --> 00:16:07,309
l'm fixed like no other
company in this field

45
00:16:07,452 --> 00:16:10,615
and that's because my Coyote Hills
well has just come in.

46
00:16:10,756 --> 00:16:13,190
l have a string of tools
all ready to put to work.

47
00:16:13,291 --> 00:16:15,418
l can load a rig onto trucks
and have them here in a week.

48
00:16:15,560 --> 00:16:17,090
l have business connections

49
00:16:17,090 --> 00:16:18,620
so l can get the lumber
for the derricks.

50
00:16:18,764 --> 00:16:20,647
Such things go by friendship

51
00:16:20,647 --> 00:16:22,530
in a rush like this.

52
00:16:22,668 --> 00:16:23,393
And this is why l can

53
00:16:23,393 --> 00:16:26,502
guarantee to start drilling

54
00:16:26,638 --> 00:16:29,573
and to put up the cash
to back my word.

55
00:16:29,675 --> 00:16:31,233
l assure you, ladies and gentlemen,

56
00:16:31,343 --> 00:16:34,642
no matter what the others
promise to do,

57
00:16:34,780 --> 00:16:38,181
when it comes to the showdown,
they won't be there.

58
00:16:39,451 --> 00:16:42,420
Sit down! Sit down,
you have no right...

59
00:16:43,288 --> 00:16:44,256
Let us discuss
what the man has to say.

60
00:16:44,256 --> 00:16:45,450
Let us discuss what the
man has to say.

61
00:16:45,557 --> 00:16:47,053
Prescott, do you trust
this man?

62
00:16:47,053 --> 00:16:48,549
Let's discuss
what he has to say.

63
00:16:48,660 --> 00:16:50,389
There's logic to
what he's saying.

64
00:16:50,389 --> 00:16:52,118
How does he know?
My lot is there!

65
00:16:53,965 --> 00:16:57,093
Two or three years,
it could be ten years!

66
00:16:57,202 --> 00:16:58,766
We gain nothing
by losing our heads!

67
00:16:58,766 --> 00:17:00,330
Look at that well out there!

68
00:17:00,439 --> 00:17:01,963
Nobody's losing their heads.

69
00:17:02,941 --> 00:17:05,501
You have no business being here!

70
00:17:06,478 --> 00:17:08,946
Sit that woman down, sir!

71
00:17:10,615 --> 00:17:11,980
You can sit down.

72
00:17:12,117 --> 00:17:14,585
Mr. Plainview! Please,
Mr. Plainview.

73
00:17:15,687 --> 00:17:17,678
No, Mr. Plainview!
No, where are you going?

74
00:17:17,789 --> 00:17:19,550
l don't need the lease.
Thank you.

75
00:17:19,550 --> 00:17:20,883
But we need you.

76
00:17:20,992 --> 00:17:23,222
Too much confusion.
Thank you for your time.

77
00:17:23,328 --> 00:17:24,989
No, no, there's no confusion.

78
00:17:25,130 --> 00:17:26,499
l wouldn't take the lease

79
00:17:26,499 --> 00:17:28,793
if you gave it to me as a gift.

80
00:17:39,478 --> 00:17:42,242
Mr. Bankside, l'm not going
to waste your time.

81
00:17:42,347 --> 00:17:44,815
l'd certainly appreciate it
if you didn't waste mine.

82
00:17:44,916 --> 00:17:46,003
Now, if you wish to sign with me

83
00:17:46,003 --> 00:17:49,649
we can have a well drilling
within 10 days.

84
00:17:49,755 --> 00:17:53,156
Your lot is further north from
the discovery well up here.

85
00:17:53,325 --> 00:17:55,850
That means we'll probably
have to dig deeper.

86
00:17:55,994 --> 00:17:56,940
And if there's as much

87
00:17:56,940 --> 00:17:58,360
oil here as l think there is,

88
00:17:58,497 --> 00:18:01,489
it'll be harder to reach, but once
we find it, we can take it right out.

89
00:18:01,600 --> 00:18:06,196
We have to act quickly, because
very soon these fields will be dry.

90
00:18:06,338 --> 00:18:08,636
l need you to know
what you want to do.

91
00:18:08,740 --> 00:18:11,766
Now, because of the distance
from the discovery well,

92
00:18:11,877 --> 00:18:14,141
l'll pay you a smaller royalty
than you'd get down there

93
00:18:14,246 --> 00:18:18,080
but l'm prepared to give you
a $1 ,000 bonus on your lot.

94
00:18:18,183 --> 00:18:19,741
What kind of royalty are
you talking about?

95
00:18:19,851 --> 00:18:24,288
Onesixth, plus a guarantee to
start drilling within 10 days.

96
00:18:24,389 --> 00:18:27,620
Now, that's something you
won't find anywhere else.

97
00:18:36,535 --> 00:18:38,503
What age are your children,
ma'am?

98
00:18:38,637 --> 00:18:40,332
Ten and twelve.

99
00:18:41,473 --> 00:18:45,341
Mr. Plainview, a question,
sir. Where is your wife?

100
00:18:47,479 --> 00:18:50,312
She died in childbirth,
Mrs. Bankside.

101
00:18:51,416 --> 00:18:53,714
So it's just me and my son now.

102
00:19:00,592 --> 00:19:02,457
lt's coming in, boss!

103
00:19:02,894 --> 00:19:04,191
Hear it?

104
00:19:30,488 --> 00:19:32,183
Mr. Plainview?

105
00:19:32,290 --> 00:19:33,518
Yes?

106
00:19:35,760 --> 00:19:37,853
Are you Daniel Plainview?

107
00:19:39,764 --> 00:19:40,890
Yes.

108
00:19:42,567 --> 00:19:44,535
What can l do for you?

109
00:19:46,371 --> 00:19:48,168
You look for oil.

110
00:19:49,407 --> 00:19:50,874
That's right.

111
00:19:51,009 --> 00:19:54,035
What do you pay for a place
that has it?

112
00:19:54,179 --> 00:19:57,171
Well, that depends....
What does it depend on?

113
00:19:59,217 --> 00:20:01,048
On a lot of things.

114
00:20:01,987 --> 00:20:06,981
lf l told you l knew a place that had
oil where land could be bought cheaply,

115
00:20:07,092 --> 00:20:09,856
what do you think that
would be worth?

116
00:20:10,862 --> 00:20:15,094
l think that you should
let me know what you know

117
00:20:15,200 --> 00:20:18,328
and then we'll try and work
something out.

118
00:20:20,372 --> 00:20:22,499
Can l sit down?...Please.

119
00:20:33,652 --> 00:20:35,950
What church do you belong to?

120
00:20:41,660 --> 00:20:42,957
l...

121
00:20:45,130 --> 00:20:48,622
l enjoy all faiths. l don't belong
to one church in particular.

122
00:20:48,767 --> 00:20:52,760
l like them all. l like everything.
Where are you from?

123
00:20:52,871 --> 00:20:56,739
That would be telling you.
That's what l want to sell you.

124
00:20:59,311 --> 00:21:01,871
What are you doing in Signal Hill?

125
00:21:01,980 --> 00:21:04,380
We have oil, and it seeps
through the ground.

126
00:21:04,482 --> 00:21:06,040
Do you want to pay me to know
where it is?

127
00:21:06,151 --> 00:21:07,209
Just 'cause there's something
on the ground

128
00:21:07,319 --> 00:21:09,082
doesn't mean there's anything
beneath it.

129
00:21:09,187 --> 00:21:11,917
Why did Standard Oil buy
up land?

130
00:21:14,492 --> 00:21:16,357
ls it in California?

131
00:21:17,295 --> 00:21:20,423
Maybe....How much land did
they buy?

132
00:21:20,565 --> 00:21:23,966
l'd like it better if you didn't
think l was stupid.

133
00:21:32,410 --> 00:21:34,742
Why did you come to me?

134
00:21:34,879 --> 00:21:39,179
You just brought this well in....
That's right.

135
00:21:39,284 --> 00:21:43,584
Yes, so just give me $500
in cash right now

136
00:21:43,722 --> 00:21:46,156
and l'll tell you where it is.

137
00:21:46,257 --> 00:21:48,521
l'll tell you what l'll do,
son. l'll give you $100 now,

138
00:21:48,626 --> 00:21:51,629
and if it proves to be a
promising lease

139
00:21:51,629 --> 00:21:53,256
then give you a $1 ,000 bonus.

140
00:21:53,398 --> 00:21:55,332
Six hundred dollars.

141
00:21:58,169 --> 00:22:01,036
Tell me one thing to help me decide.
What else have you got up there?

142
00:22:01,139 --> 00:22:02,834
What do you grow?

143
00:22:02,941 --> 00:22:06,672
We have a big ranch,
but it's mostly rocks.

144
00:22:06,778 --> 00:22:09,246
Plant things. Nothing will
grow but weeds.

145
00:22:09,381 --> 00:22:10,575
What makes you think it's up?

146
00:22:10,715 --> 00:22:13,775
ls there sulfur around?
Or alkali deposits?

147
00:22:13,918 --> 00:22:16,944
Alkali nearby.
l don't know sulfur.

148
00:22:23,528 --> 00:22:25,325
ls that your son?

149
00:22:25,764 --> 00:22:27,061
Yes.

150
00:22:28,400 --> 00:22:29,662
Hi....Hi.

151
00:22:32,871 --> 00:22:35,704
Who are you?...
l'm Fletcher Hamilton.

152
00:22:35,840 --> 00:22:37,808
Nice to meet you, son.
What's your name?

153
00:22:37,909 --> 00:22:39,536
What do you do?

154
00:22:40,545 --> 00:22:42,638
l work with Mr. Plainview.

155
00:22:43,348 --> 00:22:45,077
Here's $500, son.

156
00:22:45,216 --> 00:22:49,050
You tell me something worth
hearing, this money's yours.

157
00:22:53,024 --> 00:22:56,892
l come from a town called
Little Boston in lsabella County.

158
00:22:59,064 --> 00:23:03,501
This is us, here. Spur station
here at Little Boston.

159
00:23:03,601 --> 00:23:06,593
The Sunday ranch is
what you're looking for.

160
00:23:06,704 --> 00:23:08,934
There's a sheep trail that
takes you there.

161
00:23:09,040 --> 00:23:12,009
lt's a mile out of town headed
west, not far.

162
00:23:12,143 --> 00:23:16,045
Just through a small pass
here near the base of the hills.

163
00:23:16,181 --> 00:23:18,206
You'll pass a church

164
00:23:18,206 --> 00:23:19,878
and just follow the sheep trail.

165
00:23:20,018 --> 00:23:21,847
Where's Standard buying up?

166
00:23:21,847 --> 00:23:24,148
Here and here.

167
00:23:26,324 --> 00:23:28,758
Your family name is Sunday,
yes?...That's right.

168
00:23:28,860 --> 00:23:30,327
How many's in your family?

169
00:23:30,462 --> 00:23:33,659
My father and mother and
sisters and my brother Eli.

170
00:23:33,798 --> 00:23:36,460
How many sisters do you have?...
Two.

171
00:23:36,568 --> 00:23:38,900
What's your name?...Paul.

172
00:23:39,003 --> 00:23:42,234
Does any of your family know about
the oil that you say is there?

173
00:23:42,340 --> 00:23:43,773
l don't know.

174
00:23:43,875 --> 00:23:46,469
My uncle always said there
was oil there,

175
00:23:46,611 --> 00:23:48,300
but l don't know what they

176
00:23:48,300 --> 00:23:49,079
heard or what they think.

177
00:23:49,180 --> 00:23:50,613
What do you grow?

178
00:23:50,715 --> 00:23:53,738
lt's goats. lt's a goat farm.

179
00:23:53,738 --> 00:23:55,880
l told you, nothing grows
but weeds.

180
00:23:55,987 --> 00:23:58,478
ls there water?...lt's salty.

181
00:23:58,623 --> 00:24:01,990
You drill a well, it's hard
not to get saltwater.

182
00:24:03,862 --> 00:24:07,263
The oil is there. l'm telling you.

183
00:24:11,903 --> 00:24:13,300
l want to go now, so...

184
00:24:13,300 --> 00:24:15,100
You can stay tonight.

185
00:24:15,240 --> 00:24:16,847
No, l want to go now.
l want to leave.

186
00:24:16,847 --> 00:24:19,301
Listen, Paul.

187
00:24:21,179 --> 00:24:25,946
lf l travel all the way out there and
l find that you've been lying to me,

188
00:24:26,084 --> 00:24:28,678
l'm going to find you and l'm going
to take more than my money back.

189
00:24:28,786 --> 00:24:31,016
ls that all right with you?

190
00:24:31,122 --> 00:24:33,352
Yes, sir....All right, then.

191
00:24:34,092 --> 00:24:38,222
Nice luck to you. God bless....
And to you, young man.

192
00:26:17,662 --> 00:26:19,653
There's someone coming....
Thank you, Mary.

193
00:26:29,407 --> 00:26:32,934
Good evening....Good evening.

194
00:26:35,480 --> 00:26:38,745
My name's Daniel Plainview.
This is my son, H.W.

195
00:26:39,617 --> 00:26:42,381
Are you hunting?...Hunting
for quail.

196
00:26:42,487 --> 00:26:43,113
We're told there might be a
good place.

197
00:26:43,113 --> 00:26:45,354
to camp up near
the Sunday ranch.

198
00:26:45,456 --> 00:26:47,287
This is the Sunday ranch.
You can camp here.

199
00:26:47,425 --> 00:26:50,121
Thank you. Do you have water?...
Yes.

200
00:26:51,129 --> 00:26:53,120
We heard there was an earthquake
up here a few days ago.

201
00:26:53,264 --> 00:26:55,095
ls that right?...Yes.

202
00:26:55,967 --> 00:26:59,630
Your family?...Yeah, all fine.
Thank you.

203
00:27:01,272 --> 00:27:04,708
We have goat's milk, if you'd
like....That would be fine.

204
00:27:06,744 --> 00:27:07,711
Now,

205
00:27:09,614 --> 00:27:11,738
if we set our tent away
over there

206
00:27:11,738 --> 00:27:13,675
we'd be out of your way
over there.

207
00:27:13,785 --> 00:27:15,047
That's fine.

208
00:27:15,153 --> 00:27:17,348
Ruth! Help these men and
bring them some water.

209
00:27:17,455 --> 00:27:18,888
No! H.W.

210
00:27:20,792 --> 00:27:24,250
Mr. Plainview, would you
like that milk now?

211
00:27:24,395 --> 00:27:25,753
That would be fine. Thank you.

212
00:27:25,753 --> 00:27:28,456
Mary! Bring them some milk.

213
00:27:28,599 --> 00:27:30,032
My family will help you
set up your tent.

214
00:27:30,134 --> 00:27:32,364
No, please. We set ourselves
on this camping trip.

215
00:27:32,470 --> 00:27:34,131
We have to do the camping.

216
00:27:34,272 --> 00:27:35,637
Hurry up!

217
00:27:38,609 --> 00:27:42,602
Do you have bread?...
We have potatoes.

218
00:27:42,747 --> 00:27:44,374
Potatoes would be nice,
thank you.

219
00:27:44,482 --> 00:27:45,949
l'll have them boil you up
some potatoes.

220
00:27:46,084 --> 00:27:48,382
That's all right. l thought
maybe we'd make a fire.

221
00:27:48,486 --> 00:27:50,716
l wanted to work with my son
on making a fire.

222
00:27:50,822 --> 00:27:52,756
All right. My son, Eli,
will bring you some wood.

223
00:27:52,890 --> 00:27:54,915
Thank you so much for your
hospitality, Mr. Sunday.

224
00:27:55,059 --> 00:27:57,084
Yes....And we'll be out
of your way.

225
00:27:57,195 --> 00:27:59,925
We're just hunting for quail....
Yes.

226
00:28:01,899 --> 00:28:04,060
l'm sorry we don't have
any bread....No, no, no.

227
00:28:04,168 --> 00:28:06,966
Corn doesn't fill out in the
hills here. lt's mostly rock.

228
00:28:07,105 --> 00:28:09,903
We don't have room to
raise the grain.

229
00:28:13,644 --> 00:28:15,703
Thank you, young lady.

230
00:28:40,938 --> 00:28:42,565
My name is Eli.

231
00:28:43,908 --> 00:28:45,876
Yes, you're Eli Sunday.

232
00:28:46,878 --> 00:28:48,277
Welcome.

233
00:28:51,983 --> 00:28:53,678
H.W....Eli.

234
00:28:58,990 --> 00:29:02,084
You're hunting quail?...
That's right.

235
00:29:06,364 --> 00:29:08,175
We will bring dinner.

236
00:29:08,175 --> 00:29:10,858
Thank you. Thank you so much.

237
00:30:32,950 --> 00:30:34,144
Dad!

238
00:30:34,852 --> 00:30:36,581
Dad, look at my shoe.

239
00:31:03,080 --> 00:31:05,708
That's earthquake oil.
Set loose.

240
00:31:29,240 --> 00:31:30,537
So...

241
00:31:32,143 --> 00:31:33,337
So?

242
00:31:34,211 --> 00:31:35,576
So, so.

243
00:31:36,380 --> 00:31:39,679
lf there's anything here,
we take it to the sea.

244
00:31:40,818 --> 00:31:42,362
What we do is we build a pipeline

245
00:31:42,362 --> 00:31:44,549
to Port Hueneme or Santa Paula,

246
00:31:44,655 --> 00:31:46,179
it's about 100 miles,

247
00:31:46,290 --> 00:31:48,003
and we do a deal with Union Oil

248
00:31:48,003 --> 00:31:50,192
This is what we do.

249
00:31:50,728 --> 00:31:53,697
Then we don't need the railroads
and their shipping costs anymore.

250
00:31:53,798 --> 00:31:55,197
You see?

251
00:31:58,035 --> 00:31:59,059
Yeah.

