we share in the wealth together.

500
00:48:38,034 --> 00:48:40,093
Now, before we spud in Mary's
Well Number One,

501
00:48:40,203 --> 00:48:43,366
named for the lovely Miss Mary
Sunday, here by my side,

502
00:48:43,473 --> 00:48:46,465
a proud daughter of these hills,

503
00:48:46,610 --> 00:48:50,307
l'd just like to say God bless these
honest labors of ours, and, of course,

504
00:48:50,447 --> 00:48:52,472
God bless you all.

505
00:48:52,616 --> 00:48:53,708
Amen.

506
00:48:53,817 --> 00:48:55,114
Now go.

507
00:49:00,090 --> 00:49:01,853
Won't be a minute.

508
00:49:04,928 --> 00:49:06,896
Fast as you can, H.W.

509
00:49:10,400 --> 00:49:12,527
Are you ready to do this?

510
00:49:22,379 --> 00:49:24,847
That's it, ladies and gentlemen!

511
00:49:28,752 --> 00:49:32,848
Al Rose has very generously provided
some refreshments for this occasion

512
00:49:32,956 --> 00:49:35,686
out of his own pocket. Thank you, Al.

513
00:49:36,426 --> 00:49:40,863
lf you'll all just care to help
yourselves, l'll be back in a minute.

514
00:50:53,837 --> 00:50:55,361
Mary.

515
00:50:57,040 --> 00:50:58,667
Mary Sunday.

516
00:51:01,511 --> 00:51:04,241
Do you like your new dress?...
Yes. Thank you.

517
00:51:04,347 --> 00:51:07,248
You're welcome. l thought
you'd like it.

518
00:51:08,118 --> 00:51:10,643
Are you happy l came here?...Yes.

519
00:51:12,355 --> 00:51:16,052
Your daddy doesn't hit you anymore,
does he? Does he now?

520
00:51:16,926 --> 00:51:18,791
Better not, right?

521
00:51:19,462 --> 00:51:21,453
l'll take care of you.

522
00:51:22,565 --> 00:51:27,696
No more hitting, right?
No more hitting. Now go.

523
00:51:27,837 --> 00:51:30,863
Go and play some more and
don't come back.

524
00:51:40,016 --> 00:51:41,449
Daniel?

525
00:51:45,121 --> 00:51:49,285
lt's okay, H.W. Go back to sleep.
Go on. Go back to sleep.

526
00:51:51,828 --> 00:51:52,988
Daniel.

527
00:51:55,398 --> 00:51:56,592
Daniel.

528
00:51:59,536 --> 00:52:00,798
Daniel!

529
00:52:02,372 --> 00:52:03,566
Daniel!

530
00:52:03,673 --> 00:52:04,935
What?

531
00:52:06,810 --> 00:52:08,903
Lost a man down the well.

532
00:52:13,449 --> 00:52:15,576
What man?...Joe Gundha.

533
00:52:17,587 --> 00:52:19,646
Did l know him?...No.

534
00:52:20,156 --> 00:52:21,214
What happened?

535
00:52:28,898 --> 00:52:30,297
Pick it up.

536
00:52:30,967 --> 00:52:32,559
Set the brake.

537
00:52:32,669 --> 00:52:34,967
Tie it down....Tie it on.

538
00:52:39,576 --> 00:52:40,907
Shit!

539
00:52:42,979 --> 00:52:45,777
God damn it. Where's the body?

540
00:52:46,115 --> 00:52:49,107
They're fishing it out now....
All right.

541
00:52:52,488 --> 00:52:55,116
Where's the bit?...
lt's on the deck.

542
00:53:38,668 --> 00:53:41,501
Clean him up.
Put some clothes on him.

543
00:53:42,639 --> 00:53:43,901
And...

544
00:53:45,541 --> 00:53:47,099
Set up a tent.

545
00:53:47,210 --> 00:53:51,169
Anyone goes down into the cellar,
you tell somebody. Yes?

546
00:53:51,814 --> 00:53:53,213
Yes, sir....Yes, sir.

547
00:53:57,153 --> 00:53:59,178
Shut down till midday.

548
00:54:30,486 --> 00:54:33,019
And l had a vision.

549
00:54:33,019 --> 00:54:35,890
Yes, last night, l had a vision

550
00:54:35,992 --> 00:54:38,893
and l felt God's breath move
through me.

551
00:54:42,532 --> 00:54:46,628
And it rolled down into
my stomach.

552
00:54:48,638 --> 00:54:50,503
lt sloshed around.

553
00:54:51,908 --> 00:54:55,776
And my stomach spoke in a
whisper, not a shout,

554
00:54:59,015 --> 00:55:03,213
''Touch this woman with your
hands and caress her.'' Yes.

555
00:55:07,590 --> 00:55:09,751
My dear Mrs. Hunter,

556
00:55:10,927 --> 00:55:13,259
you have arthritis, don't you?

557
00:55:13,396 --> 00:55:15,387
Yes, l do, Eli....Yes.

558
00:55:15,498 --> 00:55:19,093
The devil is in your hands,
and l will suck it out.

559
00:55:20,269 --> 00:55:24,729
Now, l will not cast this
ghost out with a fever

560
00:55:24,874 --> 00:55:29,902
for the new spirit inside me has shown
me l have a new way to communicate.

561
00:55:32,382 --> 00:55:34,407
lt is a gentle whisper.

562
00:55:40,790 --> 00:55:43,156
Get out of here, ghost.

563
00:55:45,728 --> 00:55:48,060
Get out of here, ghost.

564
00:55:50,099 --> 00:55:51,532
Get out.

565
00:55:52,135 --> 00:55:55,036
Get out of here, ghost.

566
00:55:57,407 --> 00:56:00,570
Get out of here, ghost.

567
00:56:00,710 --> 00:56:02,661
...and enter this woman's body now.

568
00:56:02,661 --> 00:56:04,612
Get out of here, ghost.

569
00:56:04,714 --> 00:56:09,549
Get out of here. Don't you dare
turn around and come back.

570
00:56:10,753 --> 00:56:12,448
For if you do,

571
00:56:12,555 --> 00:56:18,050
all the armies of my boot
will kick you in the teeth

572
00:56:18,194 --> 00:56:21,686
and you will be cast up and
thrown in the dirt

573
00:56:21,831 --> 00:56:24,197
and thrust back to perdition!

574
00:56:24,333 --> 00:56:28,030
And as long as l have teeth,
l will bite you,

575
00:56:28,171 --> 00:56:32,130
and if l have no teeth,
l will gum you!

576
00:56:32,241 --> 00:56:35,972
And as long as l have fists,
l will bash you!

577
00:56:36,079 --> 00:56:40,812
Now, get out of here, ghost!
Get out of here, ghost!

578
00:56:40,950 --> 00:56:43,976
Get out of here, ghost!

579
00:56:47,156 --> 00:56:48,748
And it left!

580
00:56:49,525 --> 00:56:51,516
Hallelujah!...Hallelujah!

581
00:56:53,062 --> 00:56:55,496
Praise the Lord and his holy
days!...Praise God!

582
00:56:55,631 --> 00:56:59,067
Amen! Thank you....Thank you,
Jesus. Thank you, God.

583
00:57:00,336 --> 00:57:02,497
My dear Mrs. Hunter.

584
00:57:06,109 --> 00:57:07,838
Dance with me.

585
00:57:15,084 --> 00:57:17,416
Thanks for coming....
lt was a wonderful sermon.

586
00:57:17,520 --> 00:57:19,920
Will l see you tomorrow?...Yes.

587
00:57:24,927 --> 00:57:25,894
Eli.

588
00:57:28,464 --> 00:57:31,262
Had a tragedy at
the well last night.

589
00:57:32,502 --> 00:57:34,197
Yes, l heard.

590
00:57:34,303 --> 00:57:36,703
Joe Gundha was a man of
considerable faith.

591
00:57:36,806 --> 00:57:41,038
So if you wish to say a few words,
his burial is at noon tomorrow.

592
00:57:41,144 --> 00:57:43,977
Daniel, this accident could
have been avoided.

593
00:57:44,113 --> 00:57:46,206
lt is terrible to think of
that well

594
00:57:46,315 --> 00:57:46,675
working away out there...

595
00:57:46,675 --> 00:57:48,180
These men work in 12hour shifts.

596
00:57:48,284 --> 00:57:49,273
unblessed....They need their rest.

597
00:57:49,418 --> 00:57:49,878
lf they don't have it, they
start to make stupid mistakes.

598
00:57:49,878 --> 00:57:51,862
l've seen the men drinking

599
00:57:51,862 --> 00:57:53,237
Don't you think that has
something to do with this?

600
00:57:53,237 --> 00:57:55,590
We need these men wellrested
to bring in this well.

601
00:57:55,725 --> 00:57:57,886
They can't get that if they're
up here listening to your gospel,

602
00:57:57,994 --> 00:58:00,121
and then the well can't produce
and blow gold all over the place.

603
00:58:00,263 --> 00:58:02,231
l wish l had more time with
Joe Gundha.

604
00:58:02,365 --> 00:58:03,559
More could have been done.

605
00:58:03,699 --> 00:58:08,693
Then the well can't produce and
blow gold all over the place.

606
00:58:15,044 --> 00:58:17,342
Now, would you see to it that
his personal possessions

607
00:58:17,446 --> 00:58:19,573
find their way back to his
family, please?

608
00:58:19,715 --> 00:58:21,182
Thank you.

609
00:58:21,717 --> 00:58:24,845
Heard you were planning
some renovations.

610
00:58:24,954 --> 00:58:27,923
Yes, our congregation is
growing strongly.

611
00:58:28,591 --> 00:58:29,925
We need more room.

612
00:58:29,925 --> 00:58:33,051
That was one goddamn hell
of a show.

613
00:58:34,197 --> 00:58:36,722
We were happy to have you,
Daniel.

614
01:00:30,346 --> 01:00:32,075
Gas, gas, gas!

615
01:00:41,157 --> 01:00:44,251
Lights out! Wait here.
Wait here. Lights out!

616
01:00:54,403 --> 01:00:56,200
Put that fire out!

617
01:01:23,065 --> 01:01:26,831
ls he hurt? H.W.!
Hand him down to me!

618
01:01:31,407 --> 01:01:33,637
Hand him down!...Here.

619
01:01:37,780 --> 01:01:39,873
Got him?...l've got him!

620
01:01:47,189 --> 01:01:48,554
Oh, God.

621
01:02:03,973 --> 01:02:05,372
Come on.

622
01:02:17,520 --> 01:02:19,078
Open the door.

623
01:02:33,903 --> 01:02:36,633
Let go. There you go.
You're safe. You're safe.

624
01:02:37,606 --> 01:02:41,440
You're safe now. l got you here.
You're safe. Let go, son.

625
01:02:42,812 --> 01:02:45,679
Tell me where it hurts. Tell me
where it hurts. Tell me where...

626
01:02:45,815 --> 01:02:47,282
Did you see this?...No.

627
01:02:47,383 --> 01:02:48,441
Tell me where it hurts.

628
01:02:48,551 --> 01:02:51,111
Where does it hurt you?
Where does it hurt you?

629
01:02:51,220 --> 01:02:52,628
l can't hear my voice.

630
01:02:52,628 --> 01:02:54,883
Were you hit in the head?

631
01:02:55,591 --> 01:03:00,119
Were you hit in the head? Tell me!
You have to tell me if you were!

632
01:03:00,229 --> 01:03:02,254
l can't hear my voice.

633
01:03:11,240 --> 01:03:13,970
l have to go and deal with this
now. You wait here for me.

634
01:03:14,076 --> 01:03:15,488
You understand?
You wait here for me.

635
01:03:15,488 --> 01:03:17,910
l'll be back.
l'll be back in a minute.

636
01:03:18,013 --> 01:03:19,173
Wait here....Don't leave!

637
01:03:19,315 --> 01:03:22,003
l'm going to take care of you.
Wait.

638
01:03:22,003 --> 01:03:23,752
Stay here, son.
l'm going to fix this.

639
01:03:23,853 --> 01:03:24,751
Don't leave!...
You're going to be fine!

640
01:03:24,854 --> 01:03:25,843
Wait for me here!

641
01:03:25,955 --> 01:03:28,947
Hold him down. Hold him down....
Don't leave!

642
01:03:31,193 --> 01:03:33,821
Got to break the cables, Daniel!

643
01:03:33,963 --> 01:03:35,828
Get me a hammer!

644
01:03:42,137 --> 01:03:43,968
Get me a hammer!

645
01:03:46,542 --> 01:03:48,237
Here you go.

646
01:04:13,569 --> 01:04:14,900
Get back!

647
01:04:52,541 --> 01:04:53,838
Michael!...Sir!

648
01:04:53,943 --> 01:04:56,377
Take Dave and two of the fellas,
pick up some hoses...

649
01:04:56,478 --> 01:05:00,414
Billy, protect the roof. Don't
wait before it gets too hot.

650
01:05:22,805 --> 01:05:25,433
What are you looking so
miserable about?

651
01:05:25,574 --> 01:05:28,407
There's a whole ocean of oil
under our feet!

652
01:05:28,544 --> 01:05:31,206
No one can get at it
except for me.

653
01:06:17,926 --> 01:06:19,518
H.W. okay?

654
01:06:20,529 --> 01:06:22,087
No, he isn't.

655
01:06:24,366 --> 01:06:26,698
Where is he?...Mess room.

656
01:08:05,901 --> 01:08:09,530
That's enough now. That's enough,
H.W. That's enough.

657
01:08:12,207 --> 01:08:15,233
Do you hear me? Can you hear
me in there?

658
01:08:21,016 --> 01:08:22,711
That's enough.

659
01:08:35,063 --> 01:08:37,827
Grab his legs....l have his legs.

660
01:08:37,933 --> 01:08:39,833
No. Nope....No, lad.

661
01:08:45,507 --> 01:08:47,168
Give me that.

662
01:08:51,413 --> 01:08:52,471
Steady. That's it.

663
01:08:52,581 --> 01:08:54,981
Easy, boy. Easy....Soon be over.

664
01:08:55,083 --> 01:08:58,849
Yeah, and that's good. Now
the other side. Turn him over.

665
01:09:02,791 --> 01:09:03,758
Almost done.

666
01:09:07,296 --> 01:09:08,763
That's it.

667
01:09:09,631 --> 01:09:12,429
Come here. lt's over. lt's over.

668
01:11:18,500 --> 01:11:20,500
Who do we know in San Francisco

669
01:11:21,500 --> 01:11:24,500
or Los Angeles,
who could work with...

670
01:11:28,500 --> 01:11:32,500
You know, we could... Someone,
a teacher for H.W.

671
01:11:36,500 --> 01:11:38,500
How could you figure out that?

672
01:11:39,500 --> 01:11:41,738
Now, call... God damn it

673
01:11:41,738 --> 01:11:43,113
God damn it, what's his name?

674
01:11:43,500 --> 01:11:44,500
Bob Brody in San Francisco?

675
01:11:46,500 --> 01:11:49,500
Call Bob Brody and get
someone down here.

676
01:11:56,500 --> 01:11:58,500
l'll do it right away.

677
01:13:06,190 --> 01:13:08,454
When do we get our money, Daniel?

678
01:13:14,498 --> 01:13:18,025
Aren't you a healer? And a
vessel for the Holy Spirit?

679
01:13:18,168 --> 01:13:21,160
When are you coming over
and make my son hear again?

680
01:13:21,305 --> 01:13:22,431
Can't you do that?

681
01:13:22,539 --> 01:13:24,507
lf you had let me bless the well,
his wouldn't have happened.

682
01:13:24,642 --> 01:13:27,440
Daniel....You shouldn't have
done that.

683
01:13:28,812 --> 01:13:33,112
You owe the Church of the
Third Revelation $5,000

684
01:13:33,217 --> 01:13:36,084
as part of the arrangement
that we made!

685
01:13:45,863 --> 01:13:50,664
Don't even try it, you little
runt! You splash around in here.

686
01:13:57,541 --> 01:13:59,441
That's it, that's it.

687
01:14:11,522 --> 01:14:14,184
l'm going to bury you underground,
Eli.

688
01:14:18,228 --> 01:14:20,822
l'm going to bury you underground.

689
01:14:52,396 --> 01:14:55,160
You are a stupid man, Abel.

690
01:14:57,001 --> 01:15:01,631
You've let someone come in
here and walk all over us.

691
01:15:03,807 --> 01:15:08,267
You let him in and do his
work here,

692
01:15:08,379 --> 01:15:12,372
and you are a stupid man for
what we could have had.

693
01:15:12,516 --> 01:15:16,452
l followed His word, Eli. l tried.

694
01:15:16,553 --> 01:15:19,283
You didn't do anything but sit down.

695
01:15:20,657 --> 01:15:23,125
You're lazy, and you're stupid.

696
01:15:26,830 --> 01:15:30,960
Do you think God is going
to save you for being stupid?

697
01:15:33,637 --> 01:15:36,197
He doesn't save stupid people,
Abel.

698
01:15:39,576 --> 01:15:44,013
l will tear you apart for what
you've done, you stupid man!

699
01:15:44,148 --> 01:15:46,446
How did he come here?
Do you really know? l know!

700
01:15:46,550 --> 01:15:49,178
Son, don't do this, please!...
Be quiet!

701
01:15:49,319 --> 01:15:54,347
Shut your mouth, Abel!
lt was your stupid son!

702
01:15:54,491 --> 01:15:58,427
lt was Paul who told him to
come here. l know it.

703
01:15:58,529 --> 01:16:00,258
He went to him and he said,

704
01:16:00,364 --> 01:16:05,097
''My stupid, weak father
will give away his lots.

705
01:16:05,202 --> 01:16:08,660
''Go and take him.''
And you let it happen.

706
01:16:13,210 --> 01:16:16,338
A stupid father to a stupid son.

707
01:16:21,985 --> 01:16:23,646
Get out of there!

708
01:16:54,351 --> 01:16:55,978
Can l help you?

709
01:16:57,554 --> 01:16:59,078
Daniel?

710
01:16:59,189 --> 01:17:02,920
Who's that?...My name is Henry.

711
01:17:03,894 --> 01:17:05,293
Yeah?

712
01:17:06,463 --> 01:17:07,862
l'm Henry.

713
01:17:09,399 --> 01:17:11,424
What can l do for you?

714
01:17:14,304 --> 01:17:18,104
l'm Henry Plainview.
l'm from Fond du Lac.

715
01:17:20,644 --> 01:17:24,478
l'm your brother,
from another mother.

716
01:17:26,750 --> 01:17:28,650
Ernest is my father.

717
01:17:32,956 --> 01:17:34,480
Who are you?

718
01:17:35,859 --> 01:17:37,087
Henry.

719
01:18:04,154 --> 01:18:08,614
Mary Branch? ls that your mother?...
Yes, sir, that's right.

720
01:18:10,861 --> 01:18:16,026
l read about your gusher in
the paper, about your success.

721
01:18:16,166 --> 01:18:19,192
You heard about my strike?
You just show up?

722
01:18:20,237 --> 01:18:22,000
Our father's dead.

723
01:18:23,640 --> 01:18:26,837
Ernest died, l heard.
l wanted to find you.

724
01:18:26,977 --> 01:18:28,604
When?

725
01:18:28,712 --> 01:18:32,307
Three months ago. l got a
letter from Annabelle.

726
01:18:33,317 --> 01:18:35,182
My sister, Annabelle?

727
01:18:37,187 --> 01:18:40,850
Where is she?...Still at home.
Fond du Lac.

728
01:18:42,593 --> 01:18:46,051
You came all the way from
Wisconsin to tell me this?

729
01:18:46,196 --> 01:18:49,222
l'm coming from New Mexico.
l've been there.

730
01:18:50,434 --> 01:18:52,299
l came to find you.

731
01:18:53,437 --> 01:18:55,496
Did you know about me?

732
01:19:03,614 --> 01:19:05,809
Do you have identification?

733
01:19:06,483 --> 01:19:08,576
Do you have this letter?

734
01:19:31,742 --> 01:19:33,801
Where are you coming from?...
From New Mexico.

735
01:19:33,910 --> 01:19:35,846
Yes, l know, but from where?

736
01:19:36,513 --> 01:19:39,539
Silver City. l've been there
for two years.

737
01:19:40,617 --> 01:19:45,418
l was trying drilling of my
own for years.

738
01:19:45,555 --> 01:19:51,960
Getting leases in Texas. Louisiana....
Anything that produced?

739
01:19:52,062 --> 01:19:55,054
No. Not like your success, no.

740
01:20:01,571 --> 01:20:04,005
Are you married?...No.

741
01:20:04,508 --> 01:20:08,501
l spent time in jail. l had
a stretch of very bad time.

742
01:20:09,179 --> 01:20:12,376
l had nothing. l was picked
up in Louisiana.

743
01:20:13,884 --> 01:20:17,513
l worked on a chain gang for
six months building roads.

744
01:20:18,055 --> 01:20:21,218
That was a very hard time.

745
01:20:22,220 --> 01:20:27,070
Are you married?

746
01:20:28,065 --> 01:20:30,499
What were you in jail for?

747
01:20:30,600 --> 01:20:35,128
Believe it or not, for all the terrible
things l've gotten myself into,

748
01:20:35,238 --> 01:20:38,765
when they picked me up,
l hadn't done anything.

749
01:20:38,875 --> 01:20:42,675
But l've done my share of things

750
01:20:44,981 --> 01:20:47,381
that shouldn't be talked about.

751
01:21:09,873 --> 01:21:12,933
Drink it. Drink it!

752
01:21:55,519 --> 01:21:56,816
Come on.

753
01:22:28,485 --> 01:22:29,782
So...

754
01:22:34,591 --> 01:22:36,354
What do you want, Henry?

755
01:22:38,795 --> 01:22:40,194
Nothing.

756
01:22:43,333 --> 01:22:47,497
lf you can spare something, l
can work for you in any way.

757
01:22:47,637 --> 01:22:51,937
l know l'll keep moving, before
long, to get back to Fond du Lac.

758
01:22:52,976 --> 01:22:55,308
Do you have any money?...Some.

759
01:22:56,413 --> 01:22:58,574
Not much....Just answer me directly.

760
01:22:58,682 --> 01:23:02,277
You say ''nothing,'' then you say
you'd like to stay and work.

761
01:23:02,385 --> 01:23:07,322
And it's better, l'd just like to
hear you say you'd like to be here.

762
01:23:08,458 --> 01:23:10,358
l'd like to be here.

763
01:23:15,699 --> 01:23:21,296
l'm a good worker. l worked cable
tool rigs, built railroads.

764
01:23:23,473 --> 01:23:25,498
l won't need any favors.

765
01:23:30,514 --> 01:23:31,640
Good.

766
01:23:57,507 --> 01:23:59,668
What did my mother know?

767
01:24:02,279 --> 01:24:03,940
l don't know if she knew and
looked the other way,

768
01:24:04,514 --> 01:24:09,042
if she never knew.

769
01:24:11,788 --> 01:24:13,551
Why did you leave?

770
01:24:15,492 --> 01:24:18,461
l know you didn't get on
with our father.

771
01:24:23,667 --> 01:24:27,398
l worked for Geological Survey
and went to Kansas.

772
01:24:29,839 --> 01:24:32,865
l couldn't stay there.
l just couldn't.

773
01:24:34,611 --> 01:24:37,136
l don't like to explain myself.

774
01:24:43,186 --> 01:24:47,418
Are you an angry man, Henry?...
About what?

775
01:24:48,258 --> 01:24:52,024
Are you envious?
Do you get envious?

776
01:24:53,330 --> 01:24:55,264
l don't think so, no.

777
01:24:59,736 --> 01:25:02,068
l have a competition in me.

778
01:25:03,306 --> 01:25:05,706
l want no one else to succeed.

779
01:25:10,747 --> 01:25:13,200
l hate most people.

780
01:25:13,200 --> 01:25:15,241
That part of me is gone.

781
01:25:16,486 --> 01:25:19,353
Working and not succeeding,

782
01:25:19,456 --> 01:25:23,449
all my failures have left me...

783
01:25:26,496 --> 01:25:28,361
l just don't care.

784
01:25:30,066 --> 01:25:32,660
Well, if it's in me, it's in you.

785
01:25:34,204 --> 01:25:37,762
There are times when
l look at people

786
01:25:37,762 --> 01:25:39,608
and l see nothing worth liking.

787
01:25:45,615 --> 01:25:49,642
l want to earn enough money l
can get away from everyone.

788
01:25:54,691 --> 01:25:57,159
What will you do about your boy?

789
01:26:04,901 --> 01:26:06,528
l don't know.

790
01:26:08,071 --> 01:26:10,505
Maybe it'll change.

791
01:26:10,674 --> 01:26:15,077
Does your sound come back to you?
l don't know. Maybe no one knows that.

792
01:26:15,211 --> 01:26:19,375
Doctor might not know that....
Where's his mother?

793
01:26:25,355 --> 01:26:28,381
l don't want to talk about
those things.

794
01:26:31,728 --> 01:26:33,958
l see the worst in people, Henry.

795
01:26:35,999 --> 01:26:39,833
l don't need to look past seeing
them to get all l need.

796
01:26:42,005 --> 01:26:45,964
l've built up my hatreds over
the years, little by little.

797
01:26:49,679 --> 01:26:53,012
Having you here gives me a
second breath of life.

798
01:26:54,250 --> 01:26:56,844
l can't keep doing this on my own

799
01:27:00,156 --> 01:27:05,219
with these people.

800
01:27:45,068 --> 01:27:47,593
Daniel! Daniel, wake up! Daniel!

801
01:29:29,939 --> 01:29:33,397
Just have to go and have a
word with the conductor.

802
01:29:34,177 --> 01:29:36,270
l'll be right back.

803
01:29:36,412 --> 01:29:41,111
You stay here. You understand?
You stay here.

804
01:29:42,185 --> 01:29:44,016
l'll be right back.

805
01:30:36,739 --> 01:30:38,570
No! No!

806
01:30:40,276 --> 01:30:41,504
No!

807
01:30:51,354 --> 01:30:52,878
Tilford!...Plainview.

808
01:30:53,022 --> 01:30:54,137
This is my brother,
Henry Plainview

809
01:30:54,137 --> 01:30:55,320
from Fond du Lac.

810
01:30:55,425 --> 01:30:57,052
H.M. Tilford. Pleasure.

811
01:30:57,193 --> 01:30:59,661
Henry Plainview. J.J. Carter.

812
01:31:01,698 --> 01:31:03,063
So...

813
01:31:03,199 --> 01:31:04,826
Shall we?...Yes.

814
01:31:13,009 --> 01:31:15,204
How's your boy?

815
01:31:15,345 --> 01:31:18,712
Thank you for asking....
ls there anything we can do?

816
01:31:18,848 --> 01:31:21,248
Thanks for asking is enough.

817
01:31:22,919 --> 01:31:24,910
So what are your plans?

818
01:31:26,689 --> 01:31:29,920
ls this about buying up my
tracts here?

819
01:31:30,059 --> 01:31:31,117
Yes.

820
01:31:31,227 --> 01:31:34,060
The cable was about my
Coyote Hills lease.

821
01:31:34,197 --> 01:31:38,361
We'd like that, too....What's
your offer on Coyote Hills?

822
01:31:38,501 --> 01:31:43,063
We'll offer 150,000 for full title
That's a deal. What's next?

823
01:31:43,906 --> 01:31:47,137
You have 1 1 ,000 acres
in Little Boston.

824
01:31:47,137 --> 01:31:48,468
You have one proven well

825
01:31:48,578 --> 01:31:50,068
that was damaged......l have
three wells proven.

826
01:31:50,213 --> 01:31:57,070
You haven't been paying attention.
That's three proven wells.

827
01:31:58,554 --> 01:32:00,454
We'll make you a millionaire
while you're sitting here

828
01:32:00,556 --> 01:32:01,903
from one minute to the next.

829
01:32:04,727 --> 01:32:07,491
And what else would l do
with myself?

830
01:32:09,232 --> 01:32:13,601
Are you asking me?...What else
would l do with myself?

831
01:32:14,237 --> 01:32:16,330
Take care of your son.

832
01:32:18,007 --> 01:32:20,475
l don't know what you would do.

833
01:32:23,079 --> 01:32:25,547
lf you were me and Standard
offered to buy what you had

834
01:32:25,681 --> 01:32:28,343
for a million dollars, why? So, why?

835
01:32:29,585 --> 01:32:30,677
You know why.

836
01:32:30,820 --> 01:32:32,651
Yeah, you fellas should just
scratch around in the dirt

837
01:32:32,755 --> 01:32:33,762
and find it like the rest of us,

838
01:32:33,762 --> 01:32:36,191
instead of buying up someone
else's hard work.

839
01:32:36,325 --> 01:32:38,259
l've scratched around the dirt,
son.

840
01:32:38,361 --> 01:32:40,352
You going to change your
shipping costs?

841
01:32:40,496 --> 01:32:43,465
We don't dictate shipping costs.
That's railroad business.

842
01:32:44,500 --> 01:32:47,128
You don't own the railroads?

843
01:32:51,140 --> 01:32:53,700
'Course you do. Of course you do.

844
01:32:55,411 --> 01:32:57,845
Where you going to put it all?

845
01:32:58,881 --> 01:33:00,314
Where?

846
01:33:02,151 --> 01:33:06,144
Build a pipeline? Make a deal
with Union Oil? Be my guest.

847
01:33:06,289 --> 01:33:07,950
But if you can't pull it off,

848
01:33:08,057 --> 01:33:12,153
you've got an ocean of oil under
your feet with nowhere to go.

849
01:33:13,162 --> 01:33:17,792
Why not turn it over to us?
We'll make you rich.

850
01:33:17,934 --> 01:33:20,232
You spend time with your boy.

851
01:33:21,304 --> 01:33:23,431
lt's a great discovery.

852
01:33:24,373 --> 01:33:26,466
Now, let us help you.

853
01:33:35,685 --> 01:33:38,779
Did you just tell me how to
run my family?

854
01:33:38,921 --> 01:33:41,116
lt might be more important now
that you've proven the field

855
01:33:41,257 --> 01:33:43,122
and we're offering to buy
you out.

856
01:33:43,259 --> 01:33:45,454
One night l'm going to come to
you, inside of your house,

857
01:33:45,595 --> 01:33:48,564
or wherever you're sleeping, and
l'm going to cut your throat.

858
01:33:48,664 --> 01:33:49,824
What?

859
01:33:50,600 --> 01:33:51,862
What are you talking about?
Have you gone crazy?

860
01:33:51,968 --> 01:33:53,265
Did you hear what l said?...
l heard what you said,

861
01:33:53,402 --> 01:33:53,841
why did you say it?

862
01:33:53,841 --> 01:33:55,870
You don't tell me about my son.

863
01:33:55,972 --> 01:33:58,167
Why are you acting insane and
threatening to cut my throat?

864
01:33:58,274 --> 01:33:59,778
You don't tell me about my son.

865
01:33:59,778 --> 01:34:01,334
l'm not telling you anything!

866
01:34:01,444 --> 01:34:02,887
l'm asking you to be reasonable.

867
01:34:02,887 --> 01:34:05,244
lf l've offended you, l apologize.

868
01:34:05,381 --> 01:34:07,542
You'll see what l can do.

869
01:34:15,324 --> 01:34:19,522
This parcel here is the 3,000
acre ranch owned by B.L. Harper.

870
01:34:19,662 --> 01:34:22,153
This is San Luis Obispo
County land.

871
01:34:22,298 --> 01:34:24,129
And from here to the coast,
it's all Union Oil.

872
01:34:24,233 --> 01:34:27,361
What's this? Why don't l own this?

873
01:34:30,339 --> 01:34:32,950
Why don't l own this?

874
01:34:32,950 --> 01:34:34,867
That's the Bandy tract.

875
01:34:35,678 --> 01:34:38,841
He was the holdout, when
we were doing the buying.

876
01:34:38,948 --> 01:34:41,382
He had hoped to speak with you.

877
01:34:45,588 --> 01:34:49,080
Can't you just build the
pipeline around this tract?

878
01:34:52,061 --> 01:34:56,122
Can l build around 50 miles
of Tehachapi mountains?

879
01:34:56,265 --> 01:34:58,790
Don't be thick in front of me,
Al.

880
01:34:59,435 --> 01:35:00,388
l can go to him again.

881
01:35:00,388 --> 01:35:03,132
No, l'll go and talk to the man.

882
01:35:03,272 --> 01:35:06,173
l'll talk to him. Show you
how it's done.

883
01:35:10,012 --> 01:35:12,446
All right. Pack it up, Henry.

884
01:35:22,792 --> 01:35:26,694
How big is his room?...He's
sharing with another boy.

885
01:35:26,829 --> 01:35:29,662
Who?...An older boy. About 12.

886
01:35:29,765 --> 01:35:32,791
He's been there for a year.
Named Ballard.

887
01:35:38,007 --> 01:35:42,410
How big is the room?...lt's a
fair size. Got enough space.

888
01:35:44,714 --> 01:35:47,945
Are you taking Henry with you
to meet Union Oil?

889
01:36:01,230 --> 01:36:03,013
Are you the son of
William Bandy?

890
01:36:03,013 --> 01:36:04,791
Grandson.

891
01:36:04,900 --> 01:36:06,663
ls he here?...No, he's out.

892
01:36:06,802 --> 01:36:07,860
Where is he?

893
01:36:08,004 --> 01:36:10,871
Told you, he's out. Now,
what do you want?

894
01:36:14,377 --> 01:36:16,357
l'm Daniel Plainview.

895
01:36:16,357 --> 01:36:18,313
l want to talk with him about
his property.

896
01:36:18,414 --> 01:36:23,283
About what?...l believe l'll
talk with him about that.

897
01:36:23,753 --> 01:36:26,187
You're that oilman, aren't
you?...That's right.

898
01:36:26,322 --> 01:36:28,290
We don't want you drilling
out here.

899
01:36:28,391 --> 01:36:31,792
l don't want it either. Now,
when will he be back?

900
01:36:31,894 --> 01:36:32,952
Few days.

901
01:36:33,062 --> 01:36:35,656
Tell him l'd like to speak
with him. Not about drilling.

902
01:36:35,765 --> 01:36:37,995
And l'll be back in a week.

903
01:38:57,106 --> 01:38:59,233
Put that in a glass case.

904
01:39:00,142 --> 01:39:02,007
Here's to Union Oil.

905
01:39:02,711 --> 01:39:03,769
Hundred miles of pipeline,

906
01:39:03,913 --> 01:39:06,347
and all the independent producers
of this great state.

907
01:39:06,449 --> 01:39:07,416
Cheers.

908
01:39:32,575 --> 01:39:35,271
There's that house in Fond du Lac

909
01:39:37,179 --> 01:39:40,444
that John Hollister built.
Do you remember it?

910
01:39:43,319 --> 01:39:46,755
l thought as a boy that was the most
beautiful house l'd ever seen,

911
01:39:46,856 --> 01:39:48,483
and l wanted it.

912
01:39:49,225 --> 01:39:51,693
l wanted to live in it.

913
01:39:51,827 --> 01:39:53,351
And eat in it.

914
01:39:54,230 --> 01:39:55,822
And clean it.

915
01:39:58,834 --> 01:40:03,134
And even as a boy, l wanted to have
children to run around in it.

916
01:40:04,840 --> 01:40:06,325
You can have anything you'd like now

917
01:40:06,325 --> 01:40:07,570
Daniel.

918
01:40:08,277 --> 01:40:09,904
And you should.

919
01:40:10,679 --> 01:40:15,343
Where are you going to build it?...
Here, maybe. Near the ocean.

920
01:40:18,254 --> 01:40:21,018
Would you make it look like
that house?

921
01:40:25,761 --> 01:40:29,219
l think if l saw that house now,
it'd make me sick.

922
01:40:35,671 --> 01:40:38,139
We can eat and get some women.

923
01:40:41,110 --> 01:40:43,237
Take them to the Peachtree dance.

924
01:40:46,982 --> 01:40:50,918
l say get liquored up and take
them to the Peachtree dance.

925
01:40:53,822 --> 01:40:55,050
Yeah.

926
01:42:14,003 --> 01:42:16,403
Can l have some money, please?

927
01:42:23,812 --> 01:42:26,212
Can l have some money, please?

928
01:43:15,297 --> 01:43:17,788
l want you to tell me something.

929
01:43:21,470 --> 01:43:22,630
What?

930
01:43:23,672 --> 01:43:27,130
What's the name of the farm
next to the Hill House?

931
01:43:38,187 --> 01:43:42,851
What was the name of the farm
next to the Hill House?

932
01:43:46,395 --> 01:43:49,387
l can't remember......
Who are you?

933
01:43:52,334 --> 01:43:54,234
l'll leave, Daniel.

934
01:43:56,004 --> 01:43:57,562
Who are you?

935
01:44:00,909 --> 01:44:02,433
l'm no one.

936
01:44:03,512 --> 01:44:05,776
Just let me get up and go.

937
01:44:08,283 --> 01:44:10,148
Do l have a brother?

938
01:44:14,123 --> 01:44:19,322
l met a man in King City
who said he was your brother.

939
01:44:21,864 --> 01:44:24,958
We were friends for months.

940
01:44:26,435 --> 01:44:28,369
Working in King City.

941
01:44:30,606 --> 01:44:33,473
And he wanted to make his
way to you, Daniel.

942
01:44:34,743 --> 01:44:36,870
We didn't have any money.

943
01:44:41,750 --> 01:44:44,014
He died of tuberculosis.

944
01:44:45,454 --> 01:44:47,285
He wasn't harmed.

945
01:44:48,323 --> 01:44:50,553
Wasn't killed, nothing bad.

946
01:44:52,394 --> 01:44:54,658
But he told me about you,

947
01:44:57,699 --> 01:44:59,997
and l just took his story,

948
01:45:03,705 --> 01:45:05,502
used his diary.

949
01:45:09,144 --> 01:45:10,111
Daniel.

950
01:45:11,747 --> 01:45:15,080
Daniel, l'm your friend.

951
01:45:17,286 --> 01:45:19,720
l'm not trying to hurt you.

952
01:45:19,855 --> 01:45:21,083
Never.

953
01:45:22,224 --> 01:45:23,748
Just survive.

954
01:45:24,293 --> 01:45:25,521
No!

955
01:48:35,150 --> 01:48:36,617
Who is it?

956
01:48:37,919 --> 01:48:39,386
l'm Bandy.

957
01:48:52,167 --> 01:48:54,032
Yes. Yes.

958
01:48:56,538 --> 01:48:58,267
William Bandy.

959
01:49:01,476 --> 01:49:04,104
Yeah, l'd like to lease your land.

960
01:49:06,548 --> 01:49:10,109
l had asked for you to come
and talk to me before.

961
01:49:10,218 --> 01:49:12,482
When you were leasing land.

962
01:49:13,722 --> 01:49:15,519
That's right, yes.

963
01:49:17,225 --> 01:49:19,750
My boy's been very sick, you know.

964
01:49:20,896 --> 01:49:23,421
This was before your boy got sick.

965
01:49:26,535 --> 01:49:31,063
Now, l know that you would
like to build a pipeline

966
01:49:31,206 --> 01:49:33,868
through my property.

967
01:49:33,975 --> 01:49:38,105
ls that right, what l've heard?...
lt's absolutely right. And,

968
01:49:38,814 --> 01:49:39,781
well...

969
01:49:41,083 --> 01:49:44,314
Eight inch pipe. lt could be
buried with your consent.

970
01:49:44,453 --> 01:49:46,978
l guarantee you absolutely
no disruption...

971
01:49:47,122 --> 01:49:48,282
God.

972
01:49:50,158 --> 01:49:52,786
God has told me what you must do.

973
01:49:57,165 --> 01:49:58,894
And what is that?

974
01:49:59,868 --> 01:50:03,770
You should be washed in the
blood of Jesus Christ.

975
01:50:05,574 --> 01:50:07,508
But l am.

976
01:50:09,044 --> 01:50:11,740
l have been washed, Mr. Bandy.
l have been.

977
01:50:11,880 --> 01:50:14,450
lt's your only way to salvation.

978
01:50:14,450 --> 01:50:17,580
And your only way for what
you want.

979
01:50:19,421 --> 01:50:22,982
You can take it at the Church
of the Third Revelation.

980
01:50:25,427 --> 01:50:27,395
l'll pay you $3,000.

981
01:50:30,031 --> 01:50:32,795
l'd like you to be part of
our church.

982
01:50:34,703 --> 01:50:36,603
l'll pay you $5,000.

983
01:50:37,706 --> 01:50:39,173
Be baptized.

984
01:50:40,542 --> 01:50:44,376
Be forgiven for the sin
that you've done.

985
01:50:48,650 --> 01:50:53,519
What sin are you referring
to, Mr. Bandy?

986
01:50:54,689 --> 01:50:56,591
My sin of drilling?

987
01:51:47,275 --> 01:51:51,268
l truly wish everyone could
be saved, don't you?

988
01:51:51,413 --> 01:51:53,313
Yes.

989
01:51:53,448 --> 01:51:56,144
l am afraid that's
just not the case.

990
01:51:57,018 --> 01:52:01,512
The doctrine of universal
salvation is a lie, is it not?

991
01:52:01,656 --> 01:52:04,284
lt's a lie....lt's a lie.

992
01:52:04,392 --> 01:52:06,138
l wish everyone could be saved

993
01:52:06,138 --> 01:52:09,159
but they won't. No, they won't.

994
01:52:09,297 --> 01:52:12,755
You will never be saved if you...

995
01:52:12,867 --> 01:52:14,835
Reject the blood.

996
01:52:15,670 --> 01:52:16,830
Good.

997
01:52:17,906 --> 01:52:22,366
Now, is there a sinner here
looking for salvation?

998
01:52:25,046 --> 01:52:26,638
A new member?

999
01:52:31,119 --> 01:52:32,882
l'll ask it again.

1000
01:52:34,889 --> 01:52:37,585
ls there a sinner here
looking for God?

1001
01:52:37,726 --> 01:52:38,886
Yes.

1002
01:52:42,998 --> 01:52:44,431
Allow me.

1003
01:52:46,668 --> 01:52:49,432
Thank you for coming,
brother Daniel.

1004
01:52:51,539 --> 01:52:53,200
Thank you, Eli.

1005
